latestIgtvVideos.caption:
If you weren’t able to shop for Eid there is nothing to worry about. Here are very simple elements you need to put together an outfit as good as new. 
• A top
• Anything with flair 
• A dupatta

latestIgtvVideos.title: What’s in my bag? 👀
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Yesterday and today combined have taken this year to a point where it is depressing beyond depressing. For the sake of my sanity I have turned off the notification for news updates on my phone. I am doing anything and everything that could potentially lift my spirit and make me feel better even if it is for a few seconds. I have been binge watching friends and eating a lot of ice cream on my couch. I hope you are doing everything that puts your soul and mind to ease. Here’s a video I shot a couple of months back, hope it gives you a little break from this havoc. Honestly, revisiting my gallery and going through pictures and videos where I was oblivious about what was to come is one things that makes me believe no matter how dark, there is going to be light at the end of the tunnel.Please be safe and most importantly, be kind to yourself🙏🏼
Lots of love,
S. .
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: DIY hair oil for dandruff treatment
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Maintaining long locks is quite a task especially when your scalp becomes a victim of seasonal dandruff.I have tried everything from medical treatment to bizarre home remedies.Onion juice,eggs, spinach water.Name it and I’ve tried it.Among the million little experiments that I’ve put my hair through,this one has worked wonders.It not only gets rid of the dandruff but it also leaves my hair feeling extremely soft.The best part is that unlike some other DIY masks this doesn’t smell odd and is extremely easy to rinse off!Win win.Use this concoction atleast twice a week for best results and let me know if you found it to be as effective as I did! 🤗
